<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8182166>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Mysmenopsis rodriguesae n. sp., genitalia. A−C, male palp. D−F, female epigynum. A, retrolateral. B, prolateral. C, ventral. D, ventral. E, posterior. F, posterior, cleared. Abbreviations, CD, copulatory ducts. Cy, cymbium. CO, copulatory openings. E, embolus. Pc, paracymbium. PP, posterior plate. S, spermathecae. St, subtegulum. T, tegulum. VP, ventral plate. Scale bars, 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8182166/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8182168>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Mysmenopsis rodriguesae n. sp., habitus. A, male dorsal. B, female dorsal. C, male abdomen, posterior. D, female abdomen, posterior. Scale bars, 0.3 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8182168/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8182172>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Mysmenopsis rodriguesae n. sp., genitalia and left male leg I. A–C, left male palp. E–G, female epigynum. A, retrolateral. B, prolateral. C, ventral apical, filled embolus. D, left male leg I, tibia and metatarsus. E, ventral. F, posterior. G, posterior, cleared. Abbreviations, CD, copulatory ducts. Cy, cymbium. CO, copulatory openings. E, embolus. Mt, metatarsus. Pc, paracymbium. PP, posterior plate. S, spermatheca. St, subtegulum. T, tegulum. Ti, tibia. VP, ventral plate. Scale bars, A, B, 0.3 mm. C, D, 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8182172/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8182202>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Distribution records of Mysmenopsis mentioned in this study." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8182202/files/figure.png" ;
